<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-735] logg4j-bom conflicting with spring-frameworkobom</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-735</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have spring-framework-bom included in my pom.xml for long time. Today, when I included log4j-bom into my pom.xml, the whole system broke. On my analysis, I have found that log4j parent pom has included all spring dependencies with 3.2.8 version.&lt;br/&gt;
Hence the pom has imported two version of spring dependendencies 4.0.4 and 3.2.8 and all unwanted dependency conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;following is debug output on maven build.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;DEBUG&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;    org.springframework:spring-test:jar:4.0.4.RELEASE:test&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;DEBUG&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;       org.springframework:spring-core:jar:3.2.8.RELEASE:test (version managed from 4.0.4.RELEASE by org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j:2.0)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
