                            <comment id="14072725" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 02:52:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Log4j has a dependency on &lt;tt&gt;3.2.8.RELEASE&lt;/tt&gt; only. What do you suggest we do? No matter which version we pick, applications mixing Spring versions, might cause a conflict.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14072744" author="jvz" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 03:18:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I have a fix for this actually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14072746" author="jvz" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 03:23:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk revision 1612986. The &lt;tt&gt;log4j-bom&lt;/tt&gt; module no longer inherits from the log4j pom.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
